text: The Federal Council (, ) is the upper house of the Austrian Parliament, representing the nine States of Austria on federal level. It is part of a bicameral legislature alongside of the National Council. It can be compared with an upper house or a senate. It is less powerful than the National Council. The Bundesrat has its seat at the Austrian Parliament Building in Vienna. The Parliament Building is where the Federal Council meets in the Hofburg. ==References== Category:Government of Austria Austria
